-- Croatia’s Podravka 2011 Net Income Rises 44% on Sales Abroad
-- B y   J a s m i n a   K u z m a n o v i c
-- 2012-01-31T16:33:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-31/croatia-s-podravka-2011-net-income-rises-44-on-sales-abroad.html
Podravka Prehrambena Industrija
d.d.,  Croatia ’s second-biggest food manufacturer, said net
income rose 44 percent last year to 121 million kuna ($20
million).  Revenue grew 3 percent to 3.6 billion kuna, the Koprivnica,
Croatia-based company said in a statement to the Zagreb stock
exchange.  To contact the reporter responsible for the story: Jasmina
Kuzmanovic in Zagreb at 
 jkuzmanovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for the story: James M. Gomez
at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  